  "description": "A person loses their job during a recession. They post about it online. The post frames the loss as a \"pivot.\" People share their own pivot stories. A minor economy of shared affect emerges: vulnerability performed as resilience, loss reframed as growth, systemic failure processed as personal transformation.",
  "name": "Californication: How Affect Closes the Loop",
